Crooked teeth or malocclusion affects one in every two people around the globe. It can significantly impair self-esteem in both adults and children. Crooked teeth can be caused by an array of factors ranging from genetics to thumb sucking, birth defects, facial injury, etc. Other than affecting your self-worth, crooked teeth can also make it difficult to chew and swallow, leading to speech defects and altering your appearance. In extreme cases, it can make it difficult to speak. However, an implant dentistry offers an array of options for teeth straightening including clear aligners, metal braces, retainers, and veneers to solve your dental woes. Orthodontic treatment for crooked teeth has undergone massive advancements since its initial days. You can choose between traditional variants or newer methods like veneers or clear aligners. It is important to consider all the available options before choosing the one that is best suited to your requirements. 